Etymology.
The new species is named in honor to the recently deceased ornithologist Dr. Jacques Marie Edme Vielliard (

1944–2010

), who worked extensively on the bioacoustics of Brazilian fauna, including frogs (e.g. 

Cardoso & Vielliard 
1990

; 

Vielliard & Cardoso 
1996

). Ariovaldo A. Giaretta is especially sorry for his death, by the loss of his former teacher and a friend.
